%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fpeople-culture%2Ftrending-china%2Farticle%2F3243392%2Ffood-faux-pas-china-diner-shocked-us60000-bill-meal-after-accidentally-posting-photo-dish-ordering%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESouth%20China%20Morning%20Post%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ms%20Wang%20deleted%20her%20post%20immediately%2C%20but%20people%20kept%20making%20new%20orders%20at%20their%20table.%20She%20assumed%20someone%20had%20downloaded%20her%20photo%20and%20continued%20making%20orders%20using%20the%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20screenshot%20of%20the%20order%20Ms%20Wang%20later%20posted%20online%2C%20people%20ordered%201%2C850%20portions%20of%20fresh%20duck%20blood%2C%202%2C580%20portions%20of%20squid%2C%20and%209%2C990%20portions%20of%20shrimp%20paste%2C%20each%20priced%20at%20a%20few%20dozen%20yuan%20(a%20few%20US%20dollars).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20did%20not%20make%20Mr%20Wang%20pay%20the%20bill%20and%20moved%20her%20to%20a%20new%20table%2C%20ignoring%20all%20the%20new%20orders%20made%20via%20the%20code.%20The%20management%20said%20it%20could%20neither%20track%20down%20the%20people%20who%20ordered%20the%20food%20nor%20stop%20people%20from%20continuing%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Wang%20considered%20it%20a%20learning%20opportunity%20and%20urged%20heightened%20awareness%20of%20information%20security%20when%20sharing%20food%20photos.%20She%20advised%20people%20to%20blur%20out%20or%20cover%20up%20QR%20codes%20in%20their%20photos%20to%20prevent%20others%20from%20using%20them%20to%20order%20food%20without%20their%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701859500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F9sgeboto_hotpot-restaurant_625x300_06_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fchinese-woman-shocked-by-60-000-bill-after-accidentally-sharing-restaurant-qr-code-4639059%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Taken%20aback%20by%20the%20surge%20in%20orders%2C%20the%20r